item.title: Kate Middleton and the 100-year history of fake photos
item.description: The Princess of Wales has barely been seen since Christmas and everyone is asking, where is Kate? The Royal Family released a photo meant to squash the rumours, but when it became obvious it had been photoshopped, the speculation just got worse. Fake photos are everywhere, and there's a long history of people doctoring them, from photocopying to photoshopping, to straight up AI... Feed: https://www.abc.net.au/feeds/9593214/podcast.xml

item.title: 99Q - Ryan Gaul
item.description: Ryan Gaul (actor, writer, improv comedian, in 'The Last O.G.' & 'Superstore') and I adjust our sails and take to the high seas in a breezy and scenic ninety-nine question interview. Join Ryan and I as we discuss his comedic idols, the majesty of bridges, pumpkin bombing, tickling wrestlers, Hall vs Oates, making out with your celebrity crushes, break dancing, 7/11 sushi, hotel candles, & the tale of Goose the golden retriever... Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/b8da314/podcast/rss
